text: Frank Vincent Booth (28 February 1916 – 28 July 1974) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League (VFL). == Notes == == External links == * *Frank Booth's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1916 births Category:1974 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players Category:Hawthorn Football Club players
